Text.string: Greetings. I'm Zer0. / You will execute on these / assassinations.
You'll be rewarded / for each and every killing. / Don't disappoint me.
Judgment from on high / falls swift on Atlas traitors. / This one's personal.
He, the betrayer; / fitting end for a turncoat. / Rot in hell, coward.
Filthy betrayer. / Fitting end for a turncoat. / Rot in hell, coward.
The Baron plays games / as he toys with life and death. / Don't play by his rules.
This, a petty king, / ruling his petty kingdom. / The game is over.
Shooting flying tinks / is just like dealing with heights: / breathe, and don't look down.
A flying menace, / permanently grounded now. / Their wings have been clipped.
A man? A monster? / Waste no time with such quandaries. / They both bleed the same.
Two sides of a coin; / both were out of their damn minds. / Two faces, one grave.
A banjo is death / in the hands of murderers. / There is no encore.
A poor pretender / to an empty throne. Send her / to an early grave.
Band of ruffians. / Their music was just awful. / I say, “Good riddance.”
Villainous duo; / if they start monologuing, / you can cut them down.
Two birds and one stone. / Their reign of terror ends here. / You are the hero.
The contracts are done! / You are a true death artist. / I am most impressed.
Despicable name. / Kill him very quickly, and / do not look it up.
You've dispatched the man. / But again, seriously, / do not look it up.
This one's Hot Karl, / with fire and flaming shield. / Literally hot.
See you in hell, sir, / where they will constantly ask, / “Hot enough for you?”
Do not rest until / their blood spills across the ground. / Today, they will fall.
A heated battle. / Press on till death, Vault Hunter. / This villain must die.
You can win this fight. / The alternative is death. / So, you have options.
Kick this person's ass. / I heard them talking that smack. / You gonna take that?
I see you fighting. / Would a haiku help at all? / No. Probably not.
Assassination. / The best job in the whole world. / I know you'll kill them.
Do not let them win. / They'd tell all their friends you suck. / And you do not suck.
Show them no mercy. / Someone wants them dead and gone. / They must really suck.
Death is your paintbrush. / This target is a canvas. / Paint your masterpiece.
A murder party. / You need no invitation. / Crash their fiesta.
Ah, Handsome Jackie. / A wannabe, through and through. / See you 'round, kiddo.
Look at this dickwad / blocking everyone's commute. / Eliminate him.
A brutish creature. / Thought he could block the roadway. / His path has ended.
Life is a rhythm, / a dance of growth and decay. / It's time for the drop.
Thought he had hot hands, / but you've slowed him to a stop. / A silence descends.
As the saying goes: / sometimes you crush the jaw, and / sometimes you get crushed.
People need gimmicks. / I understand, really, but... / three skulls is too much.
